Haneen Sami Bashir Ibrahim (Arabic; amụrụ na 29 June 2000) bụ onye Sudan na-egwu mmiri
O sonyere na asọmpi mita 50 nke ụmụ nwanyị na 2016 Summer Olympics, ebe ọ nọ n'ọnọdụ nke 84 na oge nke 36.25 sekọnd. Ọ gakwaghị na ọkara ikpeazụ
Ibrahim nwere ihe ndekọ mba na mita 50 nke ụmụ nwanyị.
N'afọ 2019, ọ nọchitere anya Sudan na 2019 World Aquatics Championships nke e mere na Gwangju, South Korea

O sonyere na asọmpi mita 50 nke ụmụ nwanyị na 100 nke ụmụ nwanyị. N'ihe omume abụọ ahụ, ọ gara n'ihu ịsọ mpi na ọkara ikpeazụ. N'afọ 2021, o sonyere na asọmpi mita 50 nke ụmụ nwanyị na 2020 Summer Olympics nke emere na Tokyo, Japan.
